# Mobile Price Range Predictor

A machine learning web application that predicts the price category of a mobile phone based on its technical specifications.

Live demo: https://streamlitfrontend-ul8y.onrender.com

---

## Overview

This project trains a classification model on mobile phone hardware specs to predict one of four price ranges:

- 0 — Low
- 1 — Medium
- 2 — High
- 3 — Premium

Key finding: RAM is the strongest predictor of price range. Screen resolution and battery power also contribute significantly, while connectivity features (Bluetooth, WiFi) have minimal impact.

---

## Tech Stack

- Machine Learning: scikit-learn
- Backend API: FastAPI + Uvicorn
- Frontend: Streamlit
- Data processing: pandas, numpy, joblib

---

## Running Locally

1. Start the API server:

       cd src/api
       uvicorn app:app --reload

2. In a separate terminal, start the UI:

       streamlit run app_ui.py

---

## Dataset

Kaggle — Mobile Price Classification:
https://www.kaggle.com/datasets/iabhishekofficial/mobile-price-classification
